    "It is quite possible to further improve the model performance if we introduce the convolutional topology and some optimization techniques such as activity normalization 3.",
    "There are many inherent constraints in biological neurons.",
    "However, our research primarily centers on effectively integrating biological observations into computational models to solve real-world computing tasks, rather than strictly adhering to all biological principles.",
    "In fact, many works on bio-inspired algorithms did not follow strict biological constraints.",
    "For example, they extend the range of the timing factors of membrane potentials 31, 61, and represent individual neurons using abstract units that communicate through continuous firing rates instead of discrete action potentials 62."
